    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "You could probably build a second version of this class that handled an arbitrary offset object rather than a fixed window, although it wouldn't be performant, as there would have to be a ton of calls back into python space.  Unless there's some trick I'm not thinking of.\nhttps://github.com/pydata/pandas/blob/master/pandas/window.pyx#L252\n\nThere was an issue about cythonized offsets, #11214, and I started a proof of concept, but never went any further with it.\nhttps://github.com/chris-b1/pandas/tree/cythonize-offset\n"
  },
