    "created_at": "2016-08-11T22:14:53Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-08-11T22:14:53Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "this is actually pretty easy. the point of `build`  as @chris-b1 [indicated](https://github.com/pydata/pandas/blob/master/pandas/window.pyx#L252). IS to create the indexers to the window, which by-definition are generally variable (they don't have to be though as that can be done more efficiently by a fixed offset window). \n\nOnce you have this window indexer (and this is pretty cheap to create), then rolling is the same. The current logic assumes a fixed differential indexer (e.g. it has a constant period regardless of the point in time).\n"
